cience, communication studies, sociology, neuroscience, human sexuality, and marketing. We wanted to assemble authors from a broad array of disciplines so that wider swaths of the theoretical and empirical literature in relationship science would be covered. The authors were given a set of instructions before writing their chapters. We requested that each chapter be structured to accomplish three goals: (a) highlighting the most important principles, ideas, and findings relevant to the topic of the chapter; (b) identifying the most important and novel emerging themes or issues relevant to the topic; and (c) proposing new, promising directions for future research"--Introduction. (PsycINFO Database Record (c) 2014 APA, all rights reserved).  aElectronic reproduction.bWashington, D.C. :cAmerican Psychological Association,d2014.nAvailable via World Wide Web.nAccess limited by licensing agreement.7s2014 dcunns  a21 44 57 0aPersonality. 0aSocial psychology. 2aPsychology, Social.1 aMikulincer, Mario.2 aAmerican Psychological Association. 0aAPA handbooks in psychology.403University of Alberta Accessuhttp://ovidsp.ovid.com/ovidweb.cgi?T=JS&NEWS=N&PAGE=toc&SEARCH=2013-35884.dd&LINKTYPE=asBody&D=psbk403MacEwan University Accessuhttp://search.ebscohost.com/direct.asp?db=pzh&jid=%22201335884%22&scope=site403Concordia University of Edmonton Accessuhttp://search.ebscohost.com/login.aspx?direct=true&db=pzh&jid=201335884&site=ehost-live  hUAINzPSYCBOOKS  hUAINmCONCORDIAzPSYCBKSCON  hUAINmGR_MAC_INTzPSYCBKSGM  aInternet AccesswLCc1i6659357-1001lINTERNETmUAINTERNETrYsYtE-RESOURCEu8/12/2014xE-BOOKzPSYCBOOKS  aInternet AccesswLCc1i6659357-2001lINTERNETmCONCORDIArYsYtE-RESOURCEu8/12/2014xE-BOOKzPSYCBKSCON  aInternet AccesswLCc1i6659357-3001lINTERNETmGR_MAC_INTrYsYtE-RESOURCEu8/12/2014xE-BOOKzPSYCBKSGM01bhttp://viaf.org/viaf/44550666